Litha Healthcare Jumps Most in Four Months on Profit Forecast

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-15T14:37:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-15/litha-healthcare-jumps-most-in-four-months-on-profit-forecast.html
  Litha Healthcare Group Ltd . advanced
the most in almost four months after saying earnings are likely
to have increased in the latest financial year.  The stock jumped 30 cents, or 13 percent, to 2.65 rand, and
traded up 19 cents, of 8.1 percent, at 2.54 rand as of 3:51 p.m.
in Johannesburg.  Headline earnings, or profit per share before one-time
items, goodwill and amortization in the 12 months ended December
are likely to be reported as much as 150 percent higher compared
with the seven months ended Dec. 31, 2009, the company said in a
stock exchange statement. The company changed its year-end from
the May 31 to Dec. 31 in 2009, according to the statement.  On an annualized basis, headline earnings for the year to
Dec. 31 would be 30 to 50 percent higher than the 12 months
ended Dec. 31, 2009. Earnings per share would be up 20 percent
to 40 percent, it said.  Litha Healthcare also said in a separate statement it
extended an agreement to supply paediatric vaccines to the South
African government until the end of the year 2016.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
